sentences.sContent: At Honghu Lake, fish spawning has been affected, said Zeng Xiaodong, leader of the Honghu marshland management office.
sentences.sContent_eng: At Honghu Lake, fish spawning has been affected, said Zeng Xiaodong, leader of the Honghu marshland management office.
sentences.sCn: 另据洪湖沼泽管理办公室的曾晓东介绍，洪湖的鱼类的产卵量也受到了很大影响。

sentences.sContent: Designed by architect Lord Norman Foster –who created the new Wembley Stadium –the airport would be a modern-day feat of British engineering built on reclaimed marshland.
sentences.sContent_eng: Designed by architect Lord Norman Foster –who created the new Wembley Stadium –the airport would be a modern-day feat of British engineering built on reclaimed marshland.
sentences.sCn: 该机场由建筑大师诺曼·福斯特爵士设计建造——他曾设计了新温布利球场——机场将建造在开垦过的沼泽地上，这也是现代英国建筑工程的一大壮举。

trans.tranOther: an area of low wet ground that is always soft
